The flavors are great. The service couldn't be friendlier. Â  I was confused the first time. Tips: Get the brown rice and don't bother getting it stir-fried in the back. The noodles are good, too, but if you're in a hurry, they take a bit longer to cook. Unless you've got a problem with a particular veggie, just get everything in your bowl. I asked for the extremely hot sauce, and I was told I might want to try something in between the two choices of hot and extremely, so (I believe this is what he did) the guy gave me hot sauce and some diced hot peppers on top. How cool? The dumpling shell isn't too thick, which is common for quick dumplings. They're filled with real ingredients, too, not just some flavor mush. Well worth it.
